This paper deals with nonmonotonic reasoning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves logical approaches and models, which are relevant to computer science logic (cs.LO). The paper discusses preferential and rational consequence relations, which are related to machine learning and decision making (cs.LG). The topic of nonmonotonic reasoning also has applications in cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper deals with propositional language, which is relevant to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
